UID:OAnWtnRwHxl4HcaDYplLV
SUMMARY:Singing Seattle: A Reading and Celebration
DTSTAMP:20260403T032246Z
DTSTART:20260402T180000Z
DESCRIPTION:Singing Seattle: A Reading and Celebration \\nThree authors rea
	d poetry and creative nonfiction that speaks to our moment\\\, followed by
	 a Q&A and book signing. Samina Najmi reads from her debut memoir-in-essay
	s Sing Me A Circle: Love\\\, Loss\\\, and a Home in Time\\\, Lena Khalaf T
	uffaha from her award-winning poetry collection Something About Living\\\,
	 and Kalehua Kim from her debut poetry collection Mele. The readings will 
	be followed by a Q&A and book signing. \\nFree admission to this event is 
	made possible with support from 4Culture.\n\nhttps://hugohouse.org/event/_
	2026-04-02/\n\nFrom Hugo House
URL:https://hugohouse.org/event/_2026-04-02/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:hugo-house
CATEGORIES:Hugo House
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:LYBlH145cpOZP3z6fZCYa
SUMMARY:Powwow Dance Classes
DTSTAMP:20260403T032246Z
DTSTART:20260402T183000Z
DESCRIPTION:We are proud to announce that Powwow Dance Classes have returne
	d! \\nThis 19 week program is open to all Indigenous families and individu
	als. Participants will dive deep into the protocols: history: and cultural
	 significance of the Powwow. This series offers a unique opportunity for d
	ancers to be honored during a special (optional) Coming Out Ceremony at th
	e 37th Annual Indian Days Powwow. \\nWorkshop Details\\n\\n📅 Dates: Thursd
	ays from February 19th through July 2nd (UPDATE: There will be class on Ma
	rch 12\\\, 2026)\\n⏰ Time: 6:30 PM to 8:30 PM\\n📍 Location: Daybreak Star 
	Cultural Center (5011 Bernie Whitebear Way: Seattle: WA)\\n🍎 Refreshments 
	provided!\\n\\nDance Styles Taught\\n\\nMens’ Styles: Grass: Fancy: and Tr
	aditional\\nWomens’ Styles: Jingle: Fancy: and Traditional\\n\\nMeet the I
	nstructors\\n\\nLauren Nabahe (Paiute Shoshone: Navajo: Mono)\\nJobey T. W
	illiams (Tulalip and Yakama)\\n\\nContact and More Information\\nFor quest
	ions or further details: please reach out via email at: Events@unitedindia
	ns.org \\nView the event flyer here: https://www.facebook.com/share/p/1KSa
	A6TiNb/\n\nhttps://unitedindians.org/event/powwow-dance-classes-2/2026-04-
	02/\n\nFrom United Indians / Daybreak Star
URL:https://unitedindians.org/event/powwow-dance-classes-2/2026-04-02/
LOCATION:Daybreak Star Indian Cultural Center\\\, 5011 Bernie Whitebear Way
	\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98199\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:united-indians-daybreak-star
CATEGORIES:United Indians / Daybreak Star
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pRK8ewkleQpSuhKwlH_QO
SUMMARY:Boutique Bellydancersize Classes
DTSTAMP:20260403T032246Z
DTSTART:20260402T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Explore the ancient & mysterious art of belly dancing\\\, with 
	Boutique Bellydancersize classes! \\nSpecialized classes. Superior core wo
	rkout. Strengthens & coordinates muscle groups in the trunk\\\, spine & ar
	ms. Improves posture & flexibility. Students will learn the basic steps\\\
	, undulations\\\, shimmies\\\, isolations\\\, tuxseem and more. \\nAll Age
	s. \\nGroup classes at Phinney Center. A focused gym that provides a sense
	 of connection. Zaphara’s classes go beyond physical fitness\\\, including
	 a broader sense of self care\\\, including sleep\\\, nutrition\\\, skin h
	ealth\\\, stress management & socializing. \\nStarts the 1st Thursday of t
	he Month \\n7:00 pm – 8:00 pm – Beginners \\n7:45 pm – 9:00 pm Intermediat
	e – Advanced \\n4 weeks: $80\\\, Drop-ins: $27 per class \\nTaught by Zaph
	ara\\\, Master Bellydance Instructor & Performer \\nSign up and pay online
	: bellydancingbyzaphara.com/classes\n\nhttps://www.phinneycenter.org/event
	/boutique-bellydancersize-classes/2026-04-02/\n\nFrom Phinney Neighborhood
	 Association (PNA)
URL:https://www.phinneycenter.org/event/boutique-bellydancersize-classes/20
	26-04-02/
LOCATION:Phinney Center Campus: Blue (upper) Building\\\, 6532 Phinney Ave.
	 N.\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98103\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:phinney-neighborhood-association
CATEGORIES:Phinney Neighborhood Association (PNA)
