BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:PSj5ZkROMoqUH_k5pbc1B
SUMMARY:Artist Reception: "Anywhere But Here" by Mia Sutanto
DTSTAMP:20260403T032246Z
DTSTART:20260509T140000Z
DESCRIPTION:Join us at the Sacred Circle Gallery Saturday May 9 2026 2 to 5
	 PM\\nUnited Indians of All Tribes Foundation invites you to a special art
	ist reception featuring Zuni Pueblo and Chinese Indonesian artist Mia Suta
	nto. Held in conjunction with our annual Mother’s Day Native Art Market th
	is event offers a unique opportunity to meet the artist and experience her
	 newest solo exhibition “Anywhere But Here” currently on view at the Daybr
	eak Star Indian Cultural Center! \\nAbout the Event\\nThe reception will f
	eature an artist talk and a chance to view Sutanto’s powerful 2 D digital 
	art and paintings. Her work explores themes of femininity mixed cultural i
	dentity and mental health awareness. Through a striking use of the color r
	ed Sutanto explores how anger can be a transformative and healthy emotion 
	while drawing attention to the strength of Indigenous women and the respon
	sibility to protect ancestral lands. \\nSpecial Announcement\\nWe are thri
	lled to share that a signature piece from this exhibition will be the feat
	ured artwork for our  37th Annual Indian Days Powwow flyer. \\nDetails\\n\
	\n\\nWhere: Sacred Circle Gallery inside Daybreak Star Indian Cultural Cen
	ter (Discovery Park) \\n\\n\\nWhen: May 9\\\, 2026 (during the Mother’s Da
	y Native Art Market) \\n\\n\\nTime: 2 PM to 5 PM \\n\\n\\nCost: Free and o
	pen to the public \\n\\n\\nThe exhibition is curated by José E. Montaño (A
	ymara Quechua) an MTV Award winning director and curator who has led 20 so
	lo exhibits at Sacred Circle Gallery since 2021.\n\nhttps://unitedindians.
	org/event/artist-reception-anywhere-but-here-by-mia-sutanto/\n\nFrom Unite
	d Indians / Daybreak Star
URL:https://unitedindians.org/event/artist-reception-anywhere-but-here-by-m
	ia-sutanto/
LOCATION:Daybreak Star Indian Cultural Center\\\, 5011 Bernie Whitebear Way
	\\\, Seattle\\\, WA\\\, 98199\\\, United States
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:united-indians-daybreak-star
CATEGORIES:United Indians / Daybreak Star
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT3H
END:VEVENT
